{"id":157,"date":"2021-04-08T18:37:31","date_gmt":"2021-04-08T13:07:31","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/?p=157"},"modified":"2021-04-08T18:49:12","modified_gmt":"2021-04-08T13:19:12","slug":"stock-buy-sell-to-maximize-profit","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/dotnet\/problem-statement\/stock-buy-sell-to-maximize-profit\/","title":{"rendered":"Stock Buy Sell to Maximize Profit"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"157\" class=\"elementor elementor-157\" data-elementor-settings=\"[]\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-8cb3aea elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"8cb3aea\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-7c267d1\" data-id=\"7c267d1\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-99cc0ed elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"99cc0ed\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Stock Buy Sell to Maximize Profit<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-16b5479 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"16b5479\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-16fde25\" data-id=\"16fde25\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ae533f5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ae533f5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>The cost of a stock on each day is given in an array, find the max profit that you can make by buying and selling in those days. For example, if the given array is [ 6, 7, 11, 8, 5, 15, 13, 18, 4, 5, 17, 15 ], the maximum profit can earned by buying on day 4, selling on day 7. Again buy on day 8 and sell on day 11. If the given array of prices is sorted in decreasing order, then profit cannot be earned at all.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-424dad6 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"424dad6\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-98d160f\" data-id=\"98d160f\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cbbf9e2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cbbf9e2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Naive approach:<\/strong>\u00a0A simple approach is to try buying the stocks and selling them on every single day when profitable and keep updating the maximum profit so far.<\/p><p>Below is the implementation of the above approach:<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-6475f85 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"6475f85\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-e7d2c4d\" data-id=\"e7d2c4d\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d55e1ca elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d55e1ca\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>using System;<br \/>using System.Linq;<br \/>\/*<br \/>* Given a list of daily stock prices, for example:<br \/>*<br \/>* [ 6, 7, 11, 8, 5, 15, 13, 18, 4, 5, 17, 15 ]<br \/>*<br \/>*<br \/>* Implement the following function that returns the maximum profit that can be made on a trade (one buy followed by one sell).<br \/>*<br \/>* In the above example, the max profit is 13 (buy at 5, sell at 18)<br \/>*\/<\/p><p>class Solution<br \/>{<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 static void Main(string[] args)<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 {<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 int profit= CalculateMaxProfit(new int[] {6, 7, 11, 8, 5, 15, 13, 18, 4, 5, 17, 15});<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Console.WriteLine($&#8221;Max profit {profit}&#8221;);<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 }<\/p><p>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 static int CalculateMaxProfit(int[] prices)<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 {<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \/\/ TODO Implementation<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 int buyAt = stocks[0];<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 int profit = 0;<\/p><p>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 foreach(var price in stocks)<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 {<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 if(buyAt &gt; price)<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 buyAt = price;<\/p><p>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 if((price &#8211; buyAt) &gt; profit)<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 profit = price &#8211; buyAt;<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 }<\/p><p>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 return profit;<br \/>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 }<br \/>}<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Stock Buy Sell to Maximize Profit The cost of a stock on each day is given in an array, find the max profit that you can make by buying and selling in those days. For example, if the given array is [ 6, 7, 11, 8, 5, 15, 13, 18, 4, 5, 17, 15 ], &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/dotnet\/problem-statement\/stock-buy-sell-to-maximize-profit\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Stock Buy Sell to Maximize Profit<\/span> Read More &raquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[12],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/157"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=157"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/157\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":161,"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/157\/revisions\/161"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=157"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/vinayaroratech.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1